					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't own a copy of Gremlins 2 to dump and emulate, but based solely on your description and the <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/profile.php?id=336" class="postlink">game's hardware</a>, I can say this:
<br />
<br />Gremlins 2 uses the MMC3 mapper. This mapper provides two independently switchable 128x64-pixel tile banks for the background (0 and 1) and four 128x32-pixel tile banks for sprites (2, 3, 4, 5). Super Mario Bros. 3, which uses the same mapper, devotes bank 2 to Mario, and it changes with Mario's frame of animation. Kirby's Adventure, which also uses the same mapper, uses another MMC3 mode with banks 2-5 for background and 0-1 for sprites, and various frames of Kirby's movement animation are swapped into bank 0 while the enemies have to share bank 1. Gremlins 2 might be using either mode.</div>

