				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Since you can build sprites with either 8x8 or 8x16 (Pick one) and have up to 64, and at most can have 8 of those building-block "sprites" per scanline, so yeah that seems good to me. You've used up all your colors with from what I can tell. The white on the eye/glove would be a whole palette color, along with the grey and black. I take it the white around him would be transparent. But I think it's a great little sprite. Blows mine out of the water for sure. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> One thing that may be a problem is that pixels that are  1 pixel wide sometimes can't really be seen easily, so you may want to try to try making everything 2 pixels wide. Although 1-pixel wide colorings can also be used as a tool to get more synthetic colors. Look at Tepples games LJ65 after you place some blocks. On emulator it just looks like separate dots but on a CRT it'd look like different colors. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

